Reasoning: The paper discusses the use of machine learning techniques for evaluating the credibility of income data based on available variables. This involves building a model and training it on provided data samples to predict the probability distribution of the exogenous variable based on endogenous variables. This falls under the domain of machine learning and data analysis, which is covered by several sub-categories in arXiv CS. Specifically, cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.ST (Statistics), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) are all relevant sub-categories for this paper.
